    "num": 111,
    "title": "The Cliff Before Dead Pool",
    "date": "Tue 10 Mar 2026 17:02 MST",
    "excerpt": "Lake Powell is at 3,530 feet — only 40 feet above the minimum power pool threshold where Glen Canyon Dam's turbines shut down. That's the real near-term danger, not dead pool at 3,370. Both reservoirs hover around one-third full. February negotiations between the seven basin states collapsed. Arizona faces the deepest cuts.",
    "url": "journal/entry-111.html",
    "featured": true
  },
